messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants an automation triggered by the office temperature rising above 78°F.
2. The device to monitor is "Ecobee - Office" with property "Temperature".
3. The condition is a COS check where Temperature > 78°F.
4. The action is to turn on the "Left Hue Light" to full brightness (On Level 255 or On with parameter Previous or 255) with a ramp rate of 5 seconds.
5. The "Left Hue Light" accepts the command "On" [DON] with parameters: level (0-255 or enum Off/Previous) and ramp rate (seconds).
6. We will send the command "On" with parameter 255 (full brightness) and ramp rate 5 seconds.
7. The automation is named meaningfully.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Left Hue Light when Office Temp Above 78F",
    "condition": {
      ">": {
        "device": "n002_t421800120477",
        "status": "Temperature",
        "value": 78,
        "uom": "fahrenheit",
        "precision": 1
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "ZB31965_011_1",
      "command": "DON",
      "parameters": [
        { "name": "", "value": 255, "uom": "level", "precision": 0 },
        { "name": "RR", "value": 5, "uom": "seconds", "precision": 0 }
      ]
    }
  }
}
